{
  "texts": [
    "The platform was believed to contain 4.25 million customer accounts, but the bank later found that only 300,000 were legitimate.",
    "The platform vendor allegedly hired a data scientist to fabricate the majority of the accounts.",
    "Similarly, Wells Fargo faced penalties when it was revealed that employees had opened at least 3.5 million new accounts using data from existing customers without their consent.",
    "By creating fake PINs and email addresses, funds were transferred from legitimate to fraudulent accounts.",
    "Fake accounts have also been a problem in the social media and online retail sectors, leading to issues like spamming, fake reviews, 80% of the time (see Table 1K)."
  ]
}